      The format should suppress both <li> rows entirely.
    -->
    <artist-talk></artist-talk>

    <reception></reception>

    <main-image
      type="file"
      path="/artgallery/images/2026/kowalski-structural-residue.jpg"
      siteName="McHenry County College" />

    <!--
      image-caption intentionally empty — caption element must not render.
    -->
    <image-caption></image-caption>

    <!--
      statement intentionally empty — Statement accordion item must not render.
      bio is populated — only the "About James Kowalski" accordion should appear.
    -->
    <statement></statement>

    <bio><![CDATA[<p>James Kowalski is a sculptor and visual artist based in Elgin, Illinois. His practice centers on the transformation of industrial and reclaimed materials, exploring themes of labor, time, and built environments. He earned his BFA from Northern Illinois University and his MFA from the University of Illinois at Chicago.</p>
<p>Kowalski has exhibited at venues throughout the Chicago area and has completed public art commissions for the cities of Elgin and Waukegan. <em>Structural Residue</em> is his first solo exhibition at McHenry County College.</p>]]></bio>

  </exhibit>


